name: DSKAppSidebars
desc: Creates a layout with two sidebars and a central content area.

name: DSKAppSidebars
desc: The state of the DSKAppSidebars widget.

name: central
desc: The central content widget.

name: createState
desc: Creates the mutable state for this widget at a given location in the tree.

name: sidebarLeft
desc: The widget to display in the left sidebar.

name: sidebarLeftDefaultsVisible
desc: Whether the left sidebar is visible by default.

name: sidebarLeftIsResizable
desc: Whether the left sidebar is resizable.

name: sidebarLeftMaxWidth
desc: The maximum width of the left sidebar.

name: sidebarLeftMinWidth
desc: The minimum width of the left sidebar.

name: sidebarRight
desc: The widget to display in the right sidebar.

name: sidebarRightDefaultsVisible
desc: Whether the right sidebar is visible by default.

name: sidebarRightWidth
desc: The width of the right sidebar.

name: DSKAppSidebarsState
desc: The state of the DSKAppSidebars widget.

name: build
desc: Describes the part of the user interface represented by this widget.

name: initState
desc: Called when this object is inserted into the tree.

name: isSidebarLeftVisible
desc: Determines whether the left sidebar is visible.

name: isSidebarRightVisible
desc: Determines whether the right sidebar is visible.

name: setSidebarLeftVisibility
desc: Controls the visibility of the left sidebar.

name: setSidebarRightVisibility
desc: Controls the visibility of the right sidebar.

name: paint
desc:
Called whenever the object needs to paint. The given Canvas has its
coordinate space configured such that the origin is at the top left of the
box. The area of the box is the size of the size argument.

name: shouldRepaint
desc:
Called whenever a new instance of the custom painter delegate class is
provided to the RenderCustomPaint object, or any time that a new
CustomPaint object is created with a new instance of the custom painter
delegate class (which amounts to the same thing, because the latter is
implemented in terms of the former).

desc:
